TY  - JOUR
AU  - Titman, Sheridan
AU  - Tiu, Cristian
T1  - Do the Best Hedge Funds Hedge?
PY  - 2011
Y1  - 2011/01/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhq105
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 24
IS  - 1
SP  - 123
EP  - 168
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We provide a simple argument that suggests that better-informed hedge funds choose to have less exposure to factor risk. Consistent with this argument, we find that hedge funds that exhibit lower R-squareds with respect to systematic factors have higher Sharpe ratios, higher information ratios, and higher alphas. They also exhibit higher manipulation-proof performance measures and charge higher fees.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhq105
ER  - 



